Tree-Dotted Plains~
Breaking the monotony of the rolling waves of grass, here the land is
dotted with a few trees, each creating an island of shade within which the
grass is much shorter.  Some of the trees are host to birds\@ nests, with the
birds themselves perched on branches and twittering at interlopers.  The
Dantaron River runs to the north, while open fields continue to the east and
west.  The Lithling Road ends at a turnpike to the west, while the river
bends towards the plains to the east.  
