route connecting the inhabitants of Lithling to the Arien Plains.  Paved
with broad, flat cobblestones and meticulously maintained by peasant
laborers, it is wide and durable enough to withstand the substantial amount
of cart traffic directed along it.  The tall sugar crops to the east
contrast starkly with the flat, watery rice plantation west of the road.  
