undulations in the ground are betrayed by the surprisingly uniform heights
of the wheat ears, which follow them with perfect fidelity.  Throughout the
fields, peasants can be seen busy at work, planting, harvesting, and
bundling the crops.  To the west, a door opens to the mill on the river.  
