An Open Field of Wheat~
The flatlands at the heart of the Lithling Valley are covered with vast
fields of golden wheat, the countless ears standing between three and four
feet high.  Each breeze ripples through the crop in sweeping waves, making
the whole look very much like an ocean.  This part of the valley is largely
empty of buildings, with the mill to the west and the manor house off in the
distance to the east being notable exceptions.  
